snippet.textDisplay:
That's some nasty stuff to be perfecting your bead on. 😂 7010 & 6010 rod can be tricky.
But you can run an open root with 6010, fire up and keep pushing it in.

7018 is less messy.

You should be able to run a nice uphill pass before downhill.
At least 1/4" plate. V-groove with a backing strip being the most common test.
snippet.textOriginal:
